<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Padua" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polysphincta sinearanea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinearanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Polysphincta sinearanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of the 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the combination of the following characters: (1) epomia present, about 0.9 times length of proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9B</figureCitation>
); (2) malar space 0.5-0.6 times as long as proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9B</figureCitation>
); (3) fore wing vein 1 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">cu-a</emphasis>
more or less interstitial relative to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9A</figureCitation>
); (4) mesosoma entirely orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9A</figureCitation>
); (5) fore wing very slightly yellowish hyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9A</figureCitation>
); (6) hind leg orange with femur, tibia and tarsus brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9A</figureCitation>
); (7) metasoma orange, with posterior margins of tergites II-IV narrowly black, posterior half of tergite V black, and tergites VI+ black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Polysphincta sinearanea Padua, 2018, ♀, paratype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550750" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9A, C</figureCitation>
); (8) ovipositor robust, 1.5 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
